- App: add new token use cases for maintainers
- App: maintainer review use cases
- Common script module, shared by assets check builds & GitHub app
- Hosting of the app




Use cases

Use cases -- contributor
- Add new token
 -- Log on with GitHub account, optionally register, authorize app, create fork repo
 -- Upload logo from local file
 -- Enter details: type, contract, name, info fields (website, desc, explorer, ...)
 -- Most frequent token types supported: Ethereum ERC20, Binance BEP2 and BEP20 (smart chain), Tron TRC10 and TRC20
 -- Shwo logo preview
 -- Check info, logo; check circulation
 -- Adjustments: logo (resize, compress), contract address (checksum)
 -- Create PR (create new branch, commit, PR)
- Pay for open PR
- Review my PR/PRs

Use cases -- maintainer
- List open PRs
- List tokens from PR (typically one, but can be more)
- Show token info (of single token or selected token)
- Show: ID, logo preview, info (if available); links to logo, info, explorer
- Search among existing tokens (using backend API)
- Show token info (of selected token)

Open:
- Refresh/recreate fork repo
